"short_span_min_tokens": {"details": {"min_tokens": 2, "token_count": 144}, "passed": true}}, "text": "3. COMMUNIST SYMPATHIZERS SEEN INCREASING IN\nSOUTH KOREA\n\nAs a result of popular dissatisfaction,\nthe number of Communist sympathizers\nin South Korea is increasing;\nif the trend\ncontinues, peaceful unification will be attained through a\ncompromise with North Korea.\n\nComment\n\nThe degree of dissatisfaction with the\nRhee administration is\nalthough\nthe army remains loyal to South Korea, 80 percent of the\ntroops would not have supported Rhee in the May elections\nhad they not been forced to do so by their officers. A leftist\ncandidate, capitalizing on the large protest vote, polled over\n2,000,000 votes against Rhee in the May elections.\n\nAlthough a significant increase in pro-Communist sentiment is unlikely, dissatisfaction with the Rhee\nregime may result in a growing susceptibility to North Korean\nproposals for a negotiated unification. Negotiations, however,\nare not likely to take place while Rhee remains in power", "token_count": 144, "token_end_0based": 143, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "3 communist sympathizers seen increasing in south korea as a result of popular dissatisfaction the number of communist sympathizers in south korea is increasing if the trend continues peaceful unification will be attained through a compromise with north korea comment the degree of dissatisfaction with the rhee administration is although the army remains loyal to south korea 80 percent of the troops would not have supported rhee in the may elections had they not been forced to do so by their officers a leftist candidate capitalizing on the large protest vote polled over 2 000 000 votes against rhee in the may elections although a significant increase in pro-communist sentiment is unlikely dissatisfaction with the rhee regime may result in a growing susceptibility to north korean proposals for a negotiated unification negotiations however are not likely to take place while rhee remains in power", "unred_source_page": 6}
